"The following are the operational requirements for a university:

"(a) Level III accreditation or its equivalent under CHBD policies for at least four (4) of its undergraduate programs, one (1) in liberal arts and one (1) in the sciences, and two (2) of its graduate programs;

"(b) Ratio of qualified full-time faculty with requisite degrees to number of students;

"(c) Adequate library and laboratories;

"(d) Research and development output of practical and commercial application to the community;

"(e) Relevant linkages and outreach programs that are of service to the community; and

"(f) Relevant academic policies, system and processes.

"The institution shall retain its status prior to the effectivity of this Act until it is able to comply with the requirements provided herein."
